-- U.S. Stocks Extend Advance as Apple Leads Rally in Tech
-- Michael P. Regan
-- 2010-06-22T15:43:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/u-s-stocks-extend-advance-as-apple-leads-technology-rally-on-ipad-sales.html

          
          
             U.S. stocks gained, led by
technology companies, after  Apple Inc . said it sold 3 million
iPads in 80 days.  
 Apple jumped 1.8 percent to $275.04, which would be a
record closing price.  
 The Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index increased 0.2 percent to
1,115.53 at 11:41 a.m. in New York after slumping as much as 0.4
percent earlier. The Dow Jones Industrial Average climbed 26.82
points, or 0.3 percent, to 10,469.23.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                                                 
                     
